Six candidates have appeared in a Machakos court on Friday for allegedly leaking the KCSE examination. The suspects, one from Kathiani Boys High School and five from Alim High School, were arrested with examination materials in their respective schools. The suspects appeared before resident magistrate K. Kenei and denied the charge. They were also charged with being in unauthorised possession of examination materials. Machakos DCIO Rodah Kanyi and other detectives arrested the suspectsÂ on Thursday evening after some sat their last paper. They were grilled at Machakos police station where they spent the night. The suspects were released on personal bonds of Sh50,000. Those who had not finished sitting their papers were allowed to continue with the exam. The students will return to court on November 29, when the case will be mentioned. Click here for the latest political news